=============================================================================================================
04/07/2021 
=============================================================================================================

A first git implementation.
The source code for INCS is implemented for a parallellization in the spatial domain for calculation of 
the scattered pressure of a point source cloud. This point source cloud is in a 3D domain and it consists of 
either polydisperse or monodisperse scatterers. They can be linear, nonlinear or microbubbles.
Moreover in this version, there is the option of computing the pressure in the whole computational domain or 
in a volume around each scatterer in order to enhance efficiency.

MPI is used for the communication between the processors. (CPU parallelization)

